# 4. PAIN POINTS (ACTIVE)
*Problems they explicitly described*

## Time/Capacity Pain

> **Alice Chin**: "Me working, you know, 80 to 100 hours a week and my team working all 35 hour weeks"

> **Eli Allison**: "I work 80 hours a week and I will say that probably half of that is admin stuff"

> **Stacey Kauffman**: "I was building PowerPoints last night until 1:30 in the morning. Like I'm not efficient at it"

> **Dr. Erica Oberg**: "If it gets me back to the gym every day, that would be a win right there"

> **Vic Partha**: "I can't max my throughput if I'm totally stuck in operations and being glued to our WhatsApp group chat, answering questions"

## Quality/Service Degradation

> **Vic Partha**: "Because I've scaled up and because, you know, I've tried to step away from operations... the quality has gone down as well. And so what's happened is our reviews have gone down"

> **Alice Chin**: "Hey, look, we're failing at this"

## Cognitive Overload

> **Kip Lynch**: "I was driving around today, it's all in my head right now"

> **Dr. Greg Eckel**: "I have open loops in my head, like, hey, what happened with this? Is this done now?"

> **Whitney Harris**: "My brain is like in overload in that like all of my system and processes that I even did have literally just been dashed"

## Training/Oversight Burden

> **Vic Partha**: "I feel like I have to be very available for my VAs"

> **Nat Bruno**: "I had to very much systemize, write down a process, do a loom video, explain everything and then even then the quality wasn't that good"

> **Dr. Greg Eckel**: "I'm following up with that. I have open loops in my head"

## Personal Life Sacrifice

> **Tyler Edwards**: "My wife wants me to have more time with our family"

> **Eliana Berger**: "Things kind of slip through the cracks. And there's definitely things also in our personal lives that we're just not getting to"

