# 7. OBJECTIONS & HESITATIONS (Overcome)

## Trust Concerns

> **Nat Bruno**: "I just didn't trust them enough to... for them to pull it off"
- **Resolution**: Ryan explains trust is built through systems: "Systems eliminate 90% of trust issues"

## Bad Past Experiences

> **Niko Kourouglos**: "I've hired the super expensive assistant. I've hired the young, new, inexpensive assistant and it's always just kind of falls flat on its face"
- **Resolution**: Different approach â€” right person + right systems + ongoing support

> **Dr. Greg Eckel**: "I've had three executive assistants since, and I just don't know how to utilize them very well"
- **Resolution**: Training and infrastructure provided, not just a person

## Financial Concerns

> **Eli Allison**: "For me it's just like you said, it's ROI and finding that money and making sure that's, you know, financially doable for the company"
- **Resolution**: "It should pay for itself"

> **Jaret Thompson**: "I got to make sure I can make the commitment. Like I told you, liquidity kind of thing right now is jamming me up a little bit"
- **Resolution**: ROI framing â€” "Everything that we do in business is about ROI"

## Skepticism About Services

> **Stacey Kauffman**: "The skepticism is like, in all the companies you've mentioned, obviously I'm very familiar with. And they all have kind of similar challenges"
- **Resolution**: Low churn rate proof (2.5% vs Magic's 45%)

## Overwhelm About Onboarding

> **Kip Lynch**: "You probably saw my face the first time you mentioned accelerator. Like, you know, all that. Like, part of it is just like the whole hurry, hurry"
- **Resolution**: Reassurance it's a process, support provided

