# 8. COMPETITORS & ALTERNATIVES MENTIONED

## Companies Named

### Magic
> **Nat Bruno**: "I think it was a company called Magic"
> **Ryan**: "Magic is sort of the puppy mill of the VA/EA world... they have a 50%, I think it was like 52% weekly churn rate"

### Wing
> **Niko Kourouglos**: "I looked at Wing... they matched me with someone and they like dumped that person on my desk"

### Athena
> **Niko Kourouglos**: "I looked at Athena... I liked the Athena model where they're like, we're going to come in and we're going to basically audit what you're doing and then we're going to build this handbook"
> **Ryan**: "They take green, new, green talent and then they spend 30 days or more, sometimes cutting corners... they install a pretty complex infrastructure that kind of makes you reliant upon them"

### Also Mentioned
- Belay
- Zirtual

## Why Alternatives Failed

> **Niko Kourouglos** (on Wing): "Basically they matched me with someone and they like dumped that person on my desk. And then I was like, okay, awesome... you just left them there"

> **Nat Bruno** (on Magic): "All of them, they were all good people... I couldn't give them an outcome or a goal and say figure it out and go do it. I had to very much systemize, write down a process, do a loom video"

> **Stacey Kauffman** (on past VAs): "They're really more of doers. Right. Whereas I need someone with a higher level"

