# 10. MISCONCEPTIONS & FALSE BELIEFS

## "I Need to Train Them on Everything"
> **Nat Bruno**: "I had to very much systemize, write down a process, do a loom video, explain everything"
- **Correction**: Assistant Launch provides trained EAs with existing systems

## "Living in Inbox = Being Effective"
> **Eliana Berger**: "I live in my inbox, so nothing's really getting past me"
- **Correction**: Ryan: "I haven't had the email app on my phone for three years and we run a 4 to 5 million dollar a year business"

## "I'm the Problem"
> **Dr. Greg Eckel**: "Maybe it's me. Maybe I'm not giving them all of the information or the system to run"
- **Correction**: Three-pronged approach needed: right person + right systems + right support

## "Complex Means I Need Complex Solutions"
> **Niko Kourouglos**: Describes elaborate multi-calendar setup as unchangeable
- **Correction**: Ryan: "I know what it looks like because I've literally dealt with hundreds of the exact same scenario"

## "VAs and EAs Are the Same"
> **Stacey Kauffman**: Had only worked with VAs
- **Correction**: Ryan: "A VA is reactive, whereas an EA is proactive. A VA is kind of a task doer generalist whereas an EA, the key differentiator is ownership"

